name: uncurl
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "uncurl" %}
{% set version = "0.0.11" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 530c9bbd4d118f4cde6194165ff484cc25b0661cd256f19e9d5fcb53fc077790

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  entry_points:
    - uncurl = uncurl.bin:main
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6
  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - pyperclip
    - six

test:
  imports:
    - uncurl
  commands:
    - pip check
    - echo "curl https://conda-forge.org/" | uncurl --help  # [not win]
    - echo \"curl https://conda-forge.org/\" | uncurl --help  # [win]
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/spulec/uncurl
  summary: A library to convert curl requests to python-requests.
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - fhoehle
